According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global POS Terminals Market was valued at USD 106.6 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 269 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 10.8% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing significant momentum as businesses across retail, hospitality, healthcare, and financial services accelerate digital transformation and adopt advanced payment technologies. The rapid expansion of contactless payments, mobile wallets, cloud-based retail management systems, and AI-powered business analytics is driving the demand for next-generation point-of-sale (POS) terminals. Increasing government initiatives promoting cashless economies and growing consumer preference for seamless payment experiences continue to strengthen long-term market prospects.
